objectives.name: Primary Safety and Tolerability Objective
objectives.text: To assess the local and systemic safety and tolerability of ABBV-951 delivered as a CSCI for 24 hours daily for up to 52 weeks.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of ABBV-951 as measured by patient-reported and rater-measured efficacy endpoints.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate PD symptoms via wearable device and biomarker research.

endpoints.name: Adverse Events
endpoints.text: Percentage of subjects with adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs) during the study

endpoints.name: Adverse Events of Special Interest
endpoints.text: Percentage of subjects with AEs of special interest (AESIs) during the study

endpoints.name: Infusion Site Evaluation Scale
endpoints.text: Percentage of subjects with numeric grade equal to or higher than 5 and percentage of subjects with letter grade equal to or higher than D on the Infusion Site Evaluation Scale at any time during the study

endpoints.name: Clinical Laboratory Test Data
endpoints.text: Change in clinical laboratory test data from Baseline to end of study

endpoints.name: Vital Sign Measurements
endpoints.text: Change in vital sign measurements from Baseline to end of study

endpoints.name: Electrocardiograms (ECGs)
endpoints.text: Change in electrocardiograms (ECGs) from Baseline to end of study

endpoints.name: PD Diary Off and On Times
endpoints.text: Average normalized daily "Off" time and "On" times as assessed by the PD Diary

endpoints.name: MDS-UPDRS Parts I-IV
endpoints.text: PD symptoms as assessed by the Movement Disorder Society-Unified Parkinson's Disease Rating Scale (MDS-UPDRS) Parts I-IV (or the UPDRS Parts I-V in countries where a validated translation of the MDS-UPDRS is not available)

endpoints.name: PDSS-2
endpoints.text: Sleep symptoms as assessed by the PD Sleep Scale-2 (PDSS-2)

endpoints.name: PDQ-39
endpoints.text: Quality of life as assessed by the PD Questionnaire-39 items (PDQ-39)

endpoints.name: EQ-5D-5L
endpoints.text: Health-related quality of life as assessed by the EuroQol 5-dimensions questionnaire (EQ-5D-5L)

endpoints.name: PKG Wearable Device
endpoints.text: PD symptoms (including tremor, bradykinesia, dyskinesia, daytime somnolence, and indication of propensity for impulsive behaviors) as assessed by the Parkinson's KinetiGraph™/Personal KinetiGraph™ (PKG) wearable device (as allowed by local regulations) from Baseline to the Week 26 Visit.

endpoints.name: Biomarker Research Endpoints
endpoints.text: Optional samples will be collected during the study to evaluate known and/or novel biomarkers related to PD, related conditions, ABBV-951, or drugs of a similar class.

estimands.name: Primary Safety Estimand - Adverse Events
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with Parkinson's Disease whose motor symptoms are inadequately controlled by current therapy (Safety Population) Summary measure: Percentage (Proportion).

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues ABBV-951 infusion prior to Week 52

intercurrentEvents.name: Death
intercurrentEvents.text: Death of the subject during the 52-week study period
